Cape Town -  A protest in the Siqalo informal settlement in Mitchells Plain turned violent on Friday morning and roads had to be closed, said the City of Cape Town's law enforcement spokesperson Wayne Dyason. "Significant damage to electrical infrastracture was done. One transformer, two distribution kiosks and one pole feeder cable were set alight and destroyed." Earlier City of Cape Town traffic spokesperson Maxine Bezuidenhout said that roads affected in Mitchells Plain were:   In a tweet DA MPL Ricardo MacKenzie blamed  “community leaders for starting a protest and preventing tens of thousands of people from #mitchellsplain getting to work.     To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
